Anonymous Fri 05 Apr 2024 06:52:41 No.64626182 Report

rad!
>>64621867 is the real answer, but from my experience, godot is great engine that packs a surprisingly huge punch. I've made MSC using godot 3.5, along with KFS using 4. GDscript is godot's native scripting language, which I found rather easy to pick up. however if you've never programmed anything before, don't fret, there are many tutorials covering the basics on how it all works. tutorials from previous engine versions will still work with the current version so as long as you fix the old syntax ("export var x" in g3 is now "@export var x" in g4, "translation" is now "position", etc. you'll see what i mean later). best of luck on your future game, anon. it takes some learning, practice, and lots of messing around but it's very fun nonetheless.
